{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:27:50.295527+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 79ab8c039c4c3d3a54677f692f847917ad9dc553)", "id": "lc_10c06310-840e-4f84-a9ca-abe60d0bfa9c"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<template>\n  <div class=\"default-page-wrapper\">\n    <DefaultNav />\n    <slot />\n    <DefaultFooter />\n  </div>\n</template>\n\n<script setup>\nimport DefaultFooter from './DefaultFooter.vue'\nimport DefaultNav from './DefaultNav.vue'\n\ndefineOptions({\n  name: 'DefaultLayout',\n})\n</script>\n\n<style lang=\"scss\">\n/* Sticky footer */\nhtml {\n  position: relative;\n  min-height: 100%;\n}\nbody {\n  margin-bottom: 60px; /* Margin bottom equal to footer height */\n}\n.default-page-wrapper {\n  padding: 5em 0em 3em 0em;\n}\n.footer {\n  position: absolute;\n  bottom: 0;\n  width: 100%;\n  height: 60px; /* Footer height */\n  line-height: 60px; /* Vertically center the text */\n  background-color: $gray-100;\n  text-align: center;\n}\n</style>\n", "id": "lc_0accbba3-3203-46f8-99eb-a6c12553e7f4"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "c0ba49f6-59c0-4223-b023-329093e7be1e", "tool_call_id": "call_44e13dcd3ef5436b9e4b06cf", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:28:00.631862+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's how this Vue 3 + Vite application bootstraps its routing and layout rendering, and how the About page gets loaded:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Application Bootstrap (`src/main.js`)\n\nThe entry point does four things in sequence:\n\n1. **Creates the Vue app** from `App.vue`.\n2. **Globally registers** the `Default` layout component under the name `LayoutDefault` — this is what makes the dynamic layout system work (more on that below).\n3. **Installs Pinia** (state management) and **Vue Router**.\n4. **Mounts** the app to `#app`.\n\n## 2. Routing (`src/router/index.js`)\n\nThe router uses **`createWebHashHistory`** (hash-based URLs like `/#/about`). Two routes are defined:\n\n| Path | Component | Loading strategy |\n|------|-----------|-----------------|\n| `/` | `Home.vue` | **Eager** — statically imported at build time |\n| `/about` | `About.vue` | **Lazy** — loaded via `() => import('../views/About.vue')` with a named chunk (`about.[hash].js`) |\n\nBoth routes carry `meta: { layout: 'default' }`. The router also sets `linkActiveClass: 'active'` for styling active nav links.\n\n## 3. Layout Rendering (`src/App.vue`)\n\n`App.vue` is the shell of the entire app. Its template is:\n\n```vue\n<component :is=\"layout\">\n  <RouterView />\n</component>\n```\n\nThe **computed property `layout`** reads `this.$route.meta.layout` and resolves it to a registered component name. For example, when `meta.layout` is `'default'`, it becomes `layout-default` — which Vue resolves to the globally registered `LayoutDefault` component (the `Default.vue` layout file).\n\nSo the rendering hierarchy is:\n\n```\nApp.vue\n  └─ <component :is=\"layout\">          ← dynamically picks the layout\n       └─ Default.vue (LayoutDefault)   ← the \"default\" layout\n            ├─ <DefaultNav />           ← navigation bar\n            ├─ <slot />                 ← ← ← THIS is where the route page goes\n            └─ <DefaultFooter />        ← footer\n                 └─ <RouterView />      ← the matched route component renders inside <slot>\n```\n\nThe `Default.vue` layout (`src/layouts/default/Default.vue`) provides a classic page wrapper: a **navigation bar** at the top, a **`<slot />`** placeholder in the middle for the current page content, and a **footer** at the bottom.\n\n## 4. How the About Page Loads\n\nWhen a user navigates to `/#/about`:\n\n1. **Vue Router matches** the `/about` route.\n2. Because the route uses a **lazy import** (`() => import('../views/About.vue')`), the browser dynamically downloads the `about.[hash].js` chunk on demand — it is *not* part of the initial bundle.\n3. The `About.vue` component is rendered inside `<RouterView />`.\n4. `App.vue`'s computed `layout` reads `this.$route.meta.layout` → `'default'` → resolves to `LayoutDefault` → so `Default.vue` wraps the page.\n5. The final DOM looks like:\n\n```\n<div class=\"default-page-wrapper\">\n  <DefaultNav />\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <h1>This is the about page</h1>\n  </div>                       ← About.vue's template (via <slot />)\n  <DefaultFooter />\n</div>\n```\n\n---\n\n**In summary:** This is a Vue 3 app with a *dynamic layout system* driven by route metadata. Every route specifies which layout to use via `meta.layout`, and `App.vue` dynamically resolves and renders that layout as a wrapper around `<RouterView />`. The About page specifically benefits from route-level code-splitting, keeping it out of the initial JavaScript bundle until a user actually visits it.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 885, "prompt_tokens": 10760, "total_tokens": 11645, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 32, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 10432, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0003229296, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 7.51296e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0002478}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871270-OZsKoabe7GkjFFHq856m", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea433-0f98-7ca1-8708-ddea112d1da0-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10760, "output_tokens": 885, "total_tokens": 11645, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 10432}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 32}}}}]}}}
